	<td bgcolor="#000000" width="100%" valign="top">
	<font face="verdana,arial,helvetica" size="1" > <b></b></font>
	<p><font face="verdana, arial, helvetica" size="2" >Solid idea's<br />
<br />
I would like to make a few comments though<br />
<br />
-I would remove evasive too, but give us a stonestance instead.<br />
<br />
-Increase taunt range to say 50ish rather then mele range. increase its refresh time maby to compinsate(if DOT taunts are added as well)<br />
<br />
-remove the 230 taunt cap, and put some mods on war items<br />
<br />
-if they keep planing to put agro procs on all our weapons(god i hate that) at least give us a AA similar to vanishing blade that is on/off. And have the procs do damage as well.<br />
<br />
I dont mind if knights are the agro kings, but they shouldnt be able to tank as well. Ok taunting skills for warriors should give us HUGE defensive skills as a tradeoff.<br />
<br />
Also my theory on SOE logic. I dont think we will see any changes till the next expansion is released(or VERY close). SoE will tend to wait till they can balance out a whole new expansion rather then going back and rebalancing a previous one. Why waste 2 weeks rebalancing stuff that will be trivial in 2 months? Least that is my theory based on the past=p. Basicaly, i would expect the same old shit at the end of the month when they release some "ideas" on melee balancing.  They will probably be good ideas, aimed at shutting people up for 2 months. Im not aiming this as a SOE hate post, but it seems to be the trend which is getting frustraiting. At least if the communication was open there wouldnt be as huge a thing(communication as in deadlines, how high of a priority, even throwing out rought ideas) about this cause we KNOW its getting worked on. As of now i dont believe SOE has even started melee balancing other then to say that it needs to be done. It would probably take a day to plan out what to do if you knew the limitations of the engine(not to mention the 1000's of posts here on the subject which help). New LDoN raids are neat and all, but considering the scope of who benifits from those vs who would benifit from these balancing its HUGE(not to mention all the bitching that would stop).<br />
<br />
<br />
Judor</font></p>
	
