	<font face="verdana, arial, helvetica" size="2" ><font color=""><b>newtank</b></font><br>
	<font face="verdana,arial,helvetica" size="1" >knows that Warriors are superior</font><br>
	<p>
&nbsp;<br>
<a href="showthread.php?postid=58475#post58475"><font face="verdana,arial,helvetica" size="1" >Post #4</font></a><br>
	<font face="verdana,arial,helvetica" size="1" >Registered: Nov 2003<br>
	Posts: 49<br><br>



	Server: Tunare<br>





                Guild: <br>



<br>	
</td>
	<td bgcolor="#000000" width="100%" valign="top">
	<font face="verdana,arial,helvetica" size="1" > <b>Re: How I'd fix warriors...</b></font>
	<p><font face="verdana, arial, helvetica" size="2" >Trading defensive/evasive for a lower but always up mitigation benifit makes sense.  By lowering the high end mitigation relative to knights the low end can be raised without sore feelings.<br />
<br />
I like the mana idea elsewhere where if you are at 0HP you dip into mana before dying so if you had 1000 mana as a non-caster that is a extra 1000 hp padding/insurance against dying.  Not sure if kei or FT should work for war with that or not...Probably should.<br />
<br />
I think a good utility option would be a bezerker like ability that increases offense as your hp declines starting from 1HP under max full health.  Add some ability to block hp out so that you can choose where your max hp are and you have a very interesting strategic choice to make.<br />
<br />
Example war with 5000 hp can choose to block say 1000  hp so that he effectively has 4000 hp but plus 200 atk or plus xxx shield or plus 15 damage shield.  This would give warriors more strategic choice without being unbalancing (the numbers are not necessary the right numbers for 1000 hp but you get the picture).  I think playing a war would be more fun if instead of focusing on increased mitigation they focus on increased utility.   Perhaps an interupt melee whereby a war can interupt a mob so it doesn't atk or lower the mobs atk thus allowing warriors to stack better in non-tanking roles.  As long as their is some drawback to the utility there is a lot of room to make warriors fun to play and slightly more powerful.  <br />
<br />
Another thing SOE should look at is riposte.  Riposte and parry should scale with weapon speed of the defender relative to the attacker.  Fast weapons should allow you to riposte more easily and thus be more defensive in nature.  Slow powerful weapons should be easier to riposte against and harder to riposte with.</font></p>
	
	<p></p>
	<p></p>
