	<td bgcolor="#000000" width="100%" valign="top">
	<font face="verdana,arial,helvetica" size="1" > <b></b></font>
	<p><font face="verdana, arial, helvetica" size="2" >I dont consider snap aggro as the fix, actually I'd much prefer seeing it the other way around, Knights = aggro, Warriors = survivability.<br />
<br />
But for it to be that way, our bonus has to be quite outstanding,<br />
aka permanent defensive/evasive.<br />
<br />
The problem we have now, is that Knights can tank almost as good as us, with infinite superior aggro.<br />
Give us one small skill with hate that works only every 3 minutes, and Knights will still have infinite superior aggro.<br />
<br />
Giving us 20% innate shielding is a step in the right direction, but too small, and it will require content tweeking as well...<br />
using Evasive will now go stacked with a higher shielding %.<br />
So on high raids, warriors will be overpowered for 2minutes time...<br />
yet on group levels, knights will still be the preffered choice...<br />
What is 20% shielding, when the mob is hitting on the shaman???<br />
<br />
Aggro, Survivablity and Damage, they can all be improved, but while contained within balanced limits. All while giving warriors something more to do then just, hit a certain button every minute.<br />
Disciplines, as simple as that. The melee's spells...<br />
<br />
They can give that boost of aggro we need if we got a triggerhappy shaman,<br />
they can give that boost of shielding we need if we got no shaman,<br />
they can give that boost of damage we need if we arent tanking....<br />
<br />
Most of the ideas you proposed, Raaj, can be wrapped into disciplines... only disciplines are a hell lot more flexible then skills and innate abilities.<br />
Just look at where the spells brought the casters...<br />
imagine if our disciplines were upgraded, as were the caster's spells.</font></p>
	
