	<td bgcolor="#000000" width="100%" valign="top">
	<font face="verdana,arial,helvetica" size="1" > <b></b></font>
	<p><font face="verdana, arial, helvetica" size="2" >The thing you have to keep in mind is that disciplines are what broke this class to begin with.<br />
<br />
The Innate shielding at 25% is basically half defensive - permanently. The agro skill will help with your shaman getting beat on. Having offensive disciplines unlocked will allow you to do better dps WHILE in that half-defensive state.<br />
<br />
Keeping the evasive disc in the game to stack with the 25% shielding is because it's only half defensive, and some mobs you'll want a little "bonus" for a short period of time. The def/evas discs were meant to be just that - a bonus...they were never meant to be a staple of the class.<br />
<br />
Now, when you've got this huge survivability compared to a knight (350hp from sta, an extra 20% off every items hp and ac, 25% innatea shielding, and the ability to do a little burst dps with fellstrike or mightystrike - you ALSO have your instant hate button (coupled with ae taunt). You bring ENOUGH to the group to warrant grabbing you, but not enough to totally phase out knights since your agro just isn't as good.</font></p>
	
	<p></p>
	<p></p>
