	<font face="verdana,arial,helvetica" size="1" > <b></b></font>
	<p><font face="verdana, arial, helvetica" size="2" ><blockquote><font face="verdana,arial,helvetica" size="1" >quote:</font><hr><i>Originally posted by Goladus </i><br />
<b>My theory on why it's taking so long to get this balancing done is that they are trying to figure out ways to both nerf Knights and compensate them enough so that they won't mind so much and might perhaps be more fun to play afterwards.  I don't think it's at all unreasonable for them to fix this problem by simply rearranging the way SK spells work in general, hopefully in most cases for the better although you may lose some aggro holding ability.<br />
<br />
I'm not sure if I've brought it up on these forums yet but when they nerfed mage mod rods, they also added a series of other spells that had not been originally intended to go in to the expansion(the summoned belts and proc weapons), and also increased the power of the Planar pet heal spell.<br />
<br />
I think that Warriors would also have less problem with what you guys call "snap aggro," if there was a reasonable mana(or time on raids) penalty for using it.  Warriors wouldn't need quite so many drastic changes if snap aggro was something that they had to use sparingly. </b><hr></blockquote> <br />
<br />
I think the closest they will come to nerfing knights spells is that spells that were not designed to be agro control and have no effect may be nerfed.  For example fear spells that are always resisted just as the low level 10 pts dot had its agro nerfed.  But in general Knights agro will be greater than war agro as it has always been.  Possible exception of pally stun being nerfed.<br />
<br />
I really think warriors are more likely to be redefined away from super high mitigation unless the new expansion moves away from slow so that super mitigation means something.<br />
<br />
If war has meaningfully more mitigation than both knights then either agro or dps has to suffer.  Traditionally warriors had higher dps than knights but lower agro control.<br />
<br />
The problem is that without decent agro the rest of the group isn't able to act for some period of time and the mitigation has to be amazingly high to compensate.  Which means if mitigation goes up agro needs to go up and either dps has to go way down or warriros are totally unbalanced relative to knights.<br />
<br />
Which would you prefer?<br />
<br />
A)  Defensive warrior with constant ~25% advantage over knights on mitigation.  Good agro control but consistantly 25% or more lower dps.  Loss of Defensive and evasive. Mana pool acts as last resort HP and at 0HP you dip into mana.<br />
<br />
B)  Defensive warrior with constant ~25% advantage over knights on mitigation constant agro control issues.  Higher long term DPS than knights good long term agro control. Loss of Defensive and evasive.<br />
<br />
C)  Warrior with DECREASED mitigation. Loss of Defensive and evasive.  Much higher DPS and utility.  Damage shield type ability.  Improved shielding abilities.  Mob debuff abilities.  Bezerker type survivability with real increased dps as hp declines.  Some form of increased soloing abilities.  Mana pool acts as last resort HP and at 0HP you dip into mana.  similiar agro with sk.<br />
<br />
D)  Ability to rapidly scale between A,B and C with penalty for doing so.  Traditionaly pally-&gt;A, SK-&gt;C and War-&gt;B but if B isn't working make warriors able to scale between A,B,&C with a penalty to offset the utility.<br />
<br />
E) Warrrior retain defensive/evasive and supream role in raids as tank.  Knights retain supream role as exp tank.  Warriors get minor upgrade from SOE but all your present issues remain.  Quarm is made 50% more dps war gets 50% better mitigatimon and the uber guilds can still use pally to tank quarm.<br />
<br />
F) Warriors are made supream raid tank and supream EXP tank SK and pally gain ability to solo like old school necro.  All sk and pally are lvl 65 with maxxed AA in no time chosen over warriros as exp tanks.<br />
<br />
I would prefer D as I think it would make warriors more interesting to play.  But I think the melee rebalancing is going to feel like a nerf to a lot of warriors who think of kunark/Velious as balanced.  Keep in mind SKs lost soloing and soloing exp as part of the tradeoff with higher dps.  We have already had our nerf.</font></p>
	
	<p></p>
	<p></p>
	<p align="right"><font face="verdana,arial,helvetica" size="1" ><a href="report.php?s=&postid=58836">Report this post to a moderator</a> | IP: <a href="postings.php?s=&action=getip&postid=58836">Logged</a></font></p>
	</td>
</tr>
